						               													<description>Quick, simple luck-driven card/dice-gambling game. As part of the Series: Cirkle, dice and cards have the same symbols (cross, circle, square, triangle) and colours (yellow, green, purple, blue) as each of these games, plus one added colour (black) and symbol (target).&amp;#10;Of each symbol/colour-combination there is one of the 24 Cards and it is on one of the total 24 sides of the dice.&amp;#10;The game is played in 3 rounds, &amp;ldquo;attacking&amp;rdquo; player (with the dice) and &amp;ldquo;defending&amp;rdquo; player (with the cards) changing roles.&amp;#10;At the first round the defending player gets all the cards, chooses 4 of them and places them in front of him. The attacking player now throws his 4 dice three times and gets all the matching cards and the points on them. The cards still on the table go to the &amp;ldquo;defending&amp;rdquo; player. After 6 times, the cards are used up, and both players count their score.&amp;#10;The second round players change roles.&amp;#10;After this, the player with the higher score decides, which player gets which role in the third round. Who wins this third round, wins the whole game. In a variant, players play only two rounds and the higher total score determines the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are more rules available, one kind of &amp;ldquo;Yahtzee&amp;rdquo;, and one tactical &amp;ldquo;memory&amp;rdquo;-variant, using only the dice or the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
